## Limitations

This report is limited by the availability of current and comprehensive data on the psychological profiles of cult leaders. The sources used vary in their academic rigor, with some being community discussions or opinion pieces rather than peer-reviewed research. Additionally, the motivations of cult leaders can be highly individualistic, making it challenging to generalize findings across all cases. Further research, particularly longitudinal studies, would be beneficial in understanding the evolving nature of cult leadership motivations.